WEBVTT

00:06.140 --> 00:08.173
Oh, thank you so
much for helping me

00:08.242 --> 00:10.108
with these flyers, Spike.

00:10.177 --> 00:14.279
I'm so lucky you just happened
to be walking past the boutique.

00:14.348 --> 00:16.381
Yeah, right...

00:16.450 --> 00:18.149
just "happened to
be walking past... "

00:18.218 --> 00:19.184
Ha-ha...

00:19.253 --> 00:22.287
♪♪

00:22.356 --> 00:23.522
What'cha got here?

00:23.591 --> 00:25.324
"Lost dog?" "Balloons for sale?"
"Guitar lessons?"

00:25.392 --> 00:28.626
'Cause I found one, I need
some and yes, I<u> am</u> interested.

00:28.695 --> 00:32.363
[wailing]

00:32.432 --> 00:35.567
No, it's a call for submissions.

00:35.636 --> 00:37.535
Fashion contest
I'm organizing.

00:37.604 --> 00:40.638
A showcase for aspiring
young designers.

00:40.707 --> 00:41.773
Oh, wow!

00:41.842 --> 00:43.308
What an awesome idea.

00:43.377 --> 00:44.810
Thank you.

00:44.878 --> 00:47.545
I remember how difficult it
was to break into the fashion

00:47.614 --> 00:49.581
industry when I
was starting out.

00:49.650 --> 00:51.749
That's why the winner
of the contest

00:51.818 --> 00:55.386
will get to debut their line
in the Carousel Boutique!

00:55.455 --> 00:57.589
So selfless.

00:57.658 --> 00:59.757
So generous.

00:59.826 --> 01:02.760
I've also managed to get
esteemed fashion critic

01:02.829 --> 01:06.831
Hoity Toity and iconic fashion
photographer Photo Finish

01:06.900 --> 01:09.434
to come to Ponyville
and judge the show.

01:09.503 --> 01:14.239
And wait until you hear who
<u>else</u> is will be a judge.

01:14.308 --> 01:15.673
Countess Coloratura?

01:15.742 --> 01:16.741
Sassy Saddles?

01:16.810 --> 01:18.176
Spike?

01:18.245 --> 01:20.512
No.

01:20.581 --> 01:23.815
The third judge for the Carousel
Boutique's Couture du Futur

01:23.884 --> 01:26.784
Fashion Contest is
none other than...

01:26.853 --> 01:28.520
Applejack!

01:28.589 --> 01:29.521
What!?

01:29.590 --> 01:30.688
What!?

01:30.757 --> 01:33.224
What!?

01:33.293 --> 01:34.593
What?

01:37.531 --> 01:40.798
<i>♪ My little pony,</i>
<i>my little pony ♪</i>

01:40.867 --> 01:43.401
<i>♪ Aaaahhh ♪</i>

01:43.470 --> 01:45.637
<i>♪ My little Pony ♪</i>

01:45.706 --> 01:47.405
<i>♪ I used to wonder what</i>
<i>friendship could be. ♪</i>

01:47.474 --> 01:49.174
<i>♪ My Little Pony ♪</i>

01:49.242 --> 01:51.676
<i>♪ Until you all shared</i>
<i>its magic with me. ♪</i>

01:51.745 --> 01:53.478
<i>♪ Big adventure! ♪</i>
<i>♪ Tons of fun ♪</i>

01:53.547 --> 01:55.313
<i>♪ A beautiful heart! ♪</i>
<i>♪ Faithful and strong! ♪</i>

01:55.382 --> 01:58.249
<i>♪ Sharing kindness ♪</i>
<i>♪ it's an easy feat ♪</i>

01:58.318 --> 02:00.251
<i>♪ And magic makes it</i>
<i>all complete! ♪</i>

02:00.320 --> 02:02.387
<i>♪ To have my little pony ♪</i>

02:02.456 --> 02:05.690
<i>♪ Do you know you're all</i>
<i>my very best friends? ♪</i>

02:05.759 --> 02:08.227
♪♪

02:13.300 --> 02:14.199
What?!

02:14.268 --> 02:15.800
You already said
that, darling.

02:15.869 --> 02:17.802
I know. But I had
to say it again

02:17.871 --> 02:19.904
because that's how
confused I am.

02:19.973 --> 02:22.874
You want<u> me</u> to judge
a fashion show?

02:22.943 --> 02:25.443
I'm sure Rarity has her
reasons and once we hear them,

02:25.512 --> 02:27.512
all of this will make sense.

02:27.581 --> 02:30.715
I admit, Applejack is
an unorthodox choice.

02:30.784 --> 02:33.718
But that is precisely what
makes her an<u> inspired</u> choice.

02:33.787 --> 02:35.287
See? Now it all...

02:37.024 --> 02:38.723
still doesn't make any sense.

02:38.792 --> 02:41.726
Hoity Toity has expertise
in fabric and stitchwork.

02:41.795 --> 02:44.929
Photo Finish has an artistic
eye for shapes and colors.

02:44.998 --> 02:48.399
But sometimes we designers
forget about practicality!

02:48.468 --> 02:50.602
That's where you come in.

02:50.671 --> 02:54.005
Uh, I think I might be a
little too "practical."

02:54.074 --> 02:57.008
My closet's nothing but
twenty versions of this hat.

02:57.077 --> 02:59.677
Which tells me you're a pony
who knows what she likes.

02:59.746 --> 03:01.946
Besides, a judge
must be honest

03:02.015 --> 03:04.415
and you're the most
honest pony there is.

03:04.484 --> 03:05.917
Ask any pony,
they'll tell you.

03:05.986 --> 03:07.986
Ooh! Let me try!

03:08.055 --> 03:08.954
'Scuse me.

03:09.023 --> 03:10.722
Have you ever
heard of Applejack?

03:10.791 --> 03:12.457
The most honest
pony there is?

03:12.526 --> 03:13.558
Sure have.

03:13.627 --> 03:15.026
See?

03:15.095 --> 03:16.828
So, what do you say?

03:16.897 --> 03:19.530
Well, if I'm bein' honest...

03:19.599 --> 03:21.933
I don't think I'm the
right pony for the job.

03:22.002 --> 03:23.901
Fashion just ain't
my bag of oats.

03:23.970 --> 03:26.604
Aw Booooooo!

03:26.673 --> 03:28.740
I do understand
your hesitation.

03:28.809 --> 03:31.509
But before you say
no, sleep on it?

03:31.578 --> 03:33.278
Sure.

03:33.347 --> 03:35.280
I guess I can do
that for you.

03:35.349 --> 03:44.289
♪♪

03:44.358 --> 03:46.391
Yeah I know, Big Mac!

03:46.460 --> 03:48.227
I was just as surprised
as you are.

03:49.896 --> 03:53.665
I mean, can you imagine
me judgin' a fashion show?

03:56.970 --> 03:58.436
I'd do it!

03:58.505 --> 04:01.372
It sounds like fun getting to
see all those pretty outfits.

04:01.441 --> 04:04.008
Well, you're the exception
in our family, sugar cube.

04:04.077 --> 04:06.411
You know about
that kind of stuff.

04:06.480 --> 04:09.013
I'd be as useful as a burr
knot on a sapling tree.

04:09.082 --> 04:11.849
[grunt]

04:11.918 --> 04:17.055
Although, Rarity did say I just
had to focus on practicality.

04:17.124 --> 04:18.856
She already has
experts for the...

04:18.925 --> 04:20.958
fashion-y stuff.

04:21.027 --> 04:23.628
But I still wouldn't
know what to say.

04:23.697 --> 04:24.963
[crash]

04:27.768 --> 04:28.967
[clatter]

04:29.036 --> 04:31.736
Come on, Apple Bloom, you're
doubling our work here.

04:31.805 --> 04:33.805
Sorry.

04:33.874 --> 04:35.773
I wanted to wear a
signature hat like yours,

04:35.842 --> 04:38.343
but it's making
it harder to see.

04:38.412 --> 04:40.279
That's because
it's not like mine.

04:41.848 --> 04:44.015
You don't need a fancy
scarf to keep your hat on.

04:44.084 --> 04:45.683
Now you can see.

04:45.752 --> 04:48.052
♪♪

04:48.121 --> 04:49.354
Hyah!

04:50.690 --> 04:52.890
Wow! That is a lot better.

04:52.959 --> 04:54.459
Thanks, Applejack.

04:54.528 --> 04:55.827
Sure thing.

04:55.896 --> 04:57.362
You know what?

04:57.431 --> 04:59.764
I<u> am</u> gonna help
Rarity judge her show.

04:59.833 --> 05:02.667
I think my sensible,
everypony take on fashion

05:02.736 --> 05:04.870
is exactly what the pony
community needs.

05:06.139 --> 05:08.439
Rarity, I thought
about it some more

05:08.508 --> 05:11.409
and if you still need me,
I'd love to be a judge.

05:11.478 --> 05:14.779
Oh, I just<u> knew</u>
you'd come around!

05:14.848 --> 05:17.915
I, Photo Finish...

05:17.984 --> 05:19.684
have arrived!

05:19.753 --> 05:22.653
As has Hoity Toity.

05:22.722 --> 05:24.689
It's wonderful to see you!

05:24.758 --> 05:25.456
Kiss.

05:25.525 --> 05:25.990
Kiss.

05:26.059 --> 05:27.091
Kiss!

05:27.160 --> 05:29.694
Thank you both so
much for doing this!

05:29.763 --> 05:31.963
[kisses]

05:32.032 --> 05:36.067
We missed you at Miss Pommel's
debut in Manehattan last week.

05:36.136 --> 05:38.102
Miss Pommel is showing?

05:38.171 --> 05:40.438
I thought she was
still making costumes.

05:40.507 --> 05:41.639
You haven't heard?

05:41.708 --> 05:44.008
Everypony who is anypony
is talking about it.

05:44.077 --> 05:44.910
[knock knock]

05:47.614 --> 05:48.713
Oh, my.

05:48.782 --> 05:51.082
They're absolutely stunning.

05:51.151 --> 05:54.652
It sure is great to hear
Miss Pommel is doing so well.

05:54.721 --> 05:56.521
Who is this
who speaks?

05:56.590 --> 05:58.122
Oh, this is Applejack.

05:58.191 --> 06:00.024
Another one of the judges.

06:00.093 --> 06:01.526
So, judge.

06:01.595 --> 06:02.728
What do you think?

06:04.130 --> 06:06.564
Oh, wow...

06:06.633 --> 06:07.765
that is just...

06:07.834 --> 06:08.866
wow.

06:08.935 --> 06:10.135
These are clothes?

06:11.905 --> 06:13.971
The photo is upside-down.

06:14.040 --> 06:16.174
This is...

06:16.243 --> 06:18.876
she looks like a disco ball.

06:18.945 --> 06:21.779
Did they have to roll
her down the runway?

06:21.848 --> 06:24.182
Ha ha ha!

06:24.251 --> 06:27.185
I can't believe anypony
would actually wear this.

06:27.254 --> 06:29.654
Am I right?

06:29.723 --> 06:31.556
Oh, my!

06:31.625 --> 06:33.758
I faint!

06:33.827 --> 06:37.062
Ha ha.. uh.. so funny.

06:42.769 --> 06:45.636
Oh, gosh, I didn't
mean to make her faint.

06:45.705 --> 06:47.572
Oh, don't worry
about it, darling.

06:47.641 --> 06:48.774
Happens all the time.

06:51.211 --> 06:54.812
Besides, that dress did look
a bit like a disco ball.

06:54.881 --> 06:57.548
Although, Miss Pommel
is making the point

06:57.617 --> 06:59.050
that no matter what we wear,

06:59.118 --> 07:01.819
it<u> is</u> a costume of
some kind or another.

07:01.888 --> 07:04.489
I have no idea what
you're talkin' about.

07:04.558 --> 07:06.123
And that's OK!

07:06.192 --> 07:08.526
Let's go meet the
designers and help them

07:08.595 --> 07:09.761
get ready for the show!

07:12.165 --> 07:13.197
De-signers!

07:13.266 --> 07:14.665
Welcome!

07:14.734 --> 07:18.269
Today you will work on your
designs and we judges will offer

07:18.338 --> 07:21.873
our guidance and advice as you
prepare for tomorrow's big show!

07:21.942 --> 07:26.844
[chattering]

07:26.913 --> 07:29.147
Lily Lace, tell us
about your inspiration.

07:30.283 --> 07:31.749
You guys.

07:31.818 --> 07:33.351
This morning on my way here?

07:33.420 --> 07:35.753
I heard a bird singing<u> lit'rally</u>
the most beautiful song

07:35.822 --> 07:37.688
I'd ever heard and
I wanted to capture

07:37.757 --> 07:39.924
not so much the
bird's song exactly?

07:39.993 --> 07:43.728
But more like how the wind
<u>carried</u> the bird's song.

07:43.797 --> 07:47.699
Powerful, yet at the same
time fragile and delicate.

07:49.336 --> 07:50.801
Uh.. Huh?

07:50.870 --> 07:53.004
Next up, meet Starstreak.

07:54.975 --> 07:57.708
I'm not interested in
what's already been done,

07:57.777 --> 08:01.646
only what will
exist in the future.

08:03.883 --> 08:06.818
Tomorrow's fashion belongs
to those who hear it coming.

08:10.957 --> 08:13.058
I am Inky Rose.

08:18.331 --> 08:20.631
You have a very focused vision.

08:20.700 --> 08:23.234
A strong sense of
what you want is good.

08:23.303 --> 08:25.636
Applejack, you've
been rather quiet.

08:25.705 --> 08:26.938
What do you think?

08:28.675 --> 08:31.008
Well, it's a lot of black.

08:31.077 --> 08:32.643
It's kind of...

08:32.712 --> 08:33.745
depressing.

08:36.883 --> 08:38.149
How's this?

08:38.218 --> 08:40.918
Makes a world of difference!

08:40.987 --> 08:43.821
Maybe to fashion
experts like you,

08:43.890 --> 08:47.124
but to ponies like
me, it's still black.

08:47.193 --> 08:51.096
And I'm not sure how you wear
singing birds or the future.

08:58.972 --> 09:01.038
I don't think they
liked what I had to say.

09:01.107 --> 09:02.540
Well, that's why you're here.

09:02.608 --> 09:05.777
Fashion needs a healthy dose
of practicality now and then.

09:11.851 --> 09:13.951
Are you puttin' holes
in the clothes...

09:14.020 --> 09:15.319
on purpose?

09:15.388 --> 09:17.188
It's to create a
distressed look.

09:17.257 --> 09:19.790
More like an "old
and tattered" look.

09:19.859 --> 09:22.159
When a pony's old
clothes get holes in 'em,

09:22.228 --> 09:24.629
they don't want to go to the
store to buy<u> new</u> clothes...

09:24.698 --> 09:25.797
with holes in 'em.

09:25.866 --> 09:28.165
OK, yes, not a very
practical choice.

09:28.234 --> 09:30.302
Fashionable, but
not practical.

09:34.708 --> 09:36.774
Simply stunning.

09:36.843 --> 09:40.778
Sure it looks pretty, but
that's a lot of fabric.

09:40.847 --> 09:42.313
With the way it drags behind,

09:42.382 --> 09:44.315
it'll be covered in
dirt in no time.

09:44.384 --> 09:45.817
Thank goodness I'm here.

09:45.885 --> 09:48.820
Otherwise we'd've had holes
in clothes and dirty dresses.

09:54.961 --> 09:58.929
Of course, no look is complete
without mane and make-up!

09:58.998 --> 10:02.033
So when are you
gonna do her mane?

10:02.102 --> 10:05.069
Uh! It's already been done!

10:05.138 --> 10:06.304
You know what?

10:06.373 --> 10:08.205
I think we've given the
designers enough guidance

10:08.274 --> 10:09.774
for today.

10:09.843 --> 10:12.443
Let's.. uh.. let them
finish their work.

10:12.512 --> 10:15.680
Can't wait to see what ya'll
do for the big show tomorrow!

10:15.749 --> 10:18.315
[indignant chatter]

10:18.384 --> 10:19.817
[nervous giggle]

10:19.886 --> 10:20.985
[door closes]

10:21.054 --> 10:24.288
♪♪

10:24.357 --> 10:25.222
Hey, Applejack.

10:25.291 --> 10:26.390
On your way home?

10:26.459 --> 10:27.992
How'd the first day
of the contest go?

10:28.061 --> 10:29.227
Great!

10:29.296 --> 10:31.729
At first, I didn't
think I'd be much help,

10:31.798 --> 10:33.898
but thank goodness I signed on!

10:33.967 --> 10:37.968
Without me, they'd be doin' all
kinds of crazy fashiony things!

10:38.037 --> 10:40.337
<i>♪ [out of tune strum] ♪</i>

10:40.406 --> 10:41.572
Hey, Rarity.

10:41.641 --> 10:42.506
Applejack says the
contest is going great!

10:42.575 --> 10:44.709
Good thing she's
there, huh?

10:44.778 --> 10:46.143
Yes. Of course.

10:46.212 --> 10:48.813
Some of her thoughts
are tough to swallow,

10:48.882 --> 10:51.182
but hopefully her candor
will help the designers

10:51.251 --> 10:53.918
achieve the best
designs possible.

10:53.987 --> 10:55.352
You seem a
little stressed.

10:55.421 --> 10:56.420
Wanna try?

10:56.489 --> 10:58.923
Music is very relaxing!

10:58.992 --> 11:00.758
Sure.

11:00.827 --> 11:06.230
<i>♪ [solo rock guitar] ♪</i>

11:06.299 --> 11:09.033
Ah, much better.

11:09.102 --> 11:20.277
♪♪

11:20.346 --> 11:22.046
I can meet my goals!

11:22.115 --> 11:24.315
Today is a fresh start.

11:24.384 --> 11:26.517
Good morning, everypony!

11:26.586 --> 11:29.220
Time for final adjustments
before the show!

11:31.958 --> 11:36.060
If buttons could convey
sadness, you've done it.

11:36.129 --> 11:38.796
To me, they convey
waking up an hour early

11:38.865 --> 11:40.197
just to button them all!

11:40.266 --> 11:42.033
And that's if you could
reach most of 'em.

11:49.509 --> 11:51.275
Is this better?

11:51.344 --> 11:53.144
There ya go.

11:53.213 --> 11:55.846
Now when it's cold, you just
slide it on ya and you're set.

11:55.915 --> 11:56.948
Like a poncho.

11:58.518 --> 12:00.385
Umm. "Poncho."

12:05.325 --> 12:08.092
I attached each
feather individually.

12:08.161 --> 12:10.061
It took me for-<i> lit'rally</i> -ever.

12:12.265 --> 12:16.167
Oh, you used hoof-crossed
double-over stitches!

12:16.236 --> 12:18.569
They're perfect!

12:18.638 --> 12:20.404
Who cares if it's
stitched perfectly?

12:20.473 --> 12:22.073
You don't need
feathers on your head.

12:24.944 --> 12:27.211
[outraged cries]

12:27.280 --> 12:29.880
My little sister tried to add
some flair to her hat

12:29.949 --> 12:31.282
and guess what it got her?

12:31.350 --> 12:34.052
An extra hour of work pickin'
apples off the ground.

12:40.026 --> 12:42.193
A good start, but it needs more.

12:44.898 --> 12:45.363
No...

12:46.299 --> 12:46.831
No...

12:47.467 --> 12:48.032
No...

12:49.535 --> 12:50.835
Yes!

12:50.904 --> 12:52.937
I'd go with this one.

12:53.006 --> 12:54.238
No! This one!

12:54.307 --> 12:57.208
[Applejack laughing]

12:57.277 --> 12:58.542
Something is funny?

12:58.611 --> 13:00.911
What? Oh, no.
It's just...

13:00.980 --> 13:03.614
I mean, those belts
look the same.

13:03.683 --> 13:05.616
That one completely
changes the look.

13:05.685 --> 13:08.619
This one compliments it.

13:08.688 --> 13:10.521
You're kidding, right?

13:10.590 --> 13:12.489
Is everything OK?

13:12.558 --> 13:15.960
They're having a heated
debate about those two belts.

13:18.064 --> 13:19.630
Oooh, both good choices.

13:19.699 --> 13:22.099
No! There is no choice!

13:22.168 --> 13:24.201
They're the exact same belt!

13:24.270 --> 13:26.036
This is so silly!

13:26.105 --> 13:28.172
Fashion is ridiculous!

13:28.241 --> 13:29.640
[gasp]

13:29.709 --> 13:31.075
You don't mean that.

13:31.144 --> 13:32.176
I do.

13:32.245 --> 13:35.913
I'm sorry but that's
my honest opinion.

13:35.982 --> 13:38.082
Well, I never
would have come

13:38.151 --> 13:40.585
if I knew we were
going to be insulted.

13:43.022 --> 13:44.055
We go!

13:45.124 --> 13:48.025
No, please! Come back!

13:48.094 --> 13:50.394
If they're out, I'm out too.

13:50.463 --> 13:52.529
I didn't get into
fashion to design boring,

13:52.598 --> 13:55.232
utilitarian clothes.

13:55.301 --> 13:57.935
I want to create
elegance and drama?

13:58.004 --> 14:00.271
And this is lit'rally
the opposite of...

14:00.340 --> 14:02.540
I mean, I can't even...

14:04.444 --> 14:06.110
Yeah, no.

14:09.315 --> 14:12.049
[sobbing]

14:12.118 --> 14:13.183
What?

14:13.252 --> 14:14.452
I was just bein' honest!

14:18.057 --> 14:21.158
[grunts]

14:21.227 --> 14:22.927
Stop everything!

14:22.996 --> 14:24.228
There is no show!

14:24.297 --> 14:25.930
Take it all down!

14:27.633 --> 14:28.999
Rarity, what's going on?

14:29.068 --> 14:30.167
Is everything OK?

14:30.236 --> 14:31.368
No!

14:31.437 --> 14:33.304
It is the opposite of OK.

14:33.373 --> 14:35.606
The judges have quit; the
designers have dropped out;

14:35.675 --> 14:37.174
the show is cancelled!

14:37.243 --> 14:39.376
All my good
intentions, squashed!

14:39.445 --> 14:42.546
[sobbing]

14:42.615 --> 14:45.249
And it's all Applejack's fault!

14:45.318 --> 14:47.017
Why are you mad at me?

14:47.086 --> 14:49.420
I was just sayin'
what I thought.

14:49.489 --> 14:51.555
And isn't that why you
wanted me to be a judge?

14:51.624 --> 14:53.223
For my honesty?

14:53.292 --> 14:54.258
Of course.

14:54.326 --> 14:57.261
But you said fashion
is ridiculous!

14:57.330 --> 14:59.096
But it's my opinion.

14:59.165 --> 15:00.597
And I'm not gonna lie.

15:00.666 --> 15:03.201
Come with me!

15:05.571 --> 15:07.738
[knock knock]

15:07.807 --> 15:10.641
Oh, Rarity.

15:10.710 --> 15:12.710
What a nice surprise.

15:12.779 --> 15:16.280
Hello Strawberry Sunrise,
this is Applejack.

15:16.349 --> 15:17.715
I was wondering if you could
tell her how you feel

15:17.784 --> 15:19.350
about apples?

15:19.419 --> 15:20.584
Don't like 'em.

15:20.653 --> 15:22.353
What? Why?

15:22.422 --> 15:25.522
They're crunchy, they're
sweet, they're delicious.

15:25.591 --> 15:26.958
They're not strawberries.

15:29.328 --> 15:30.260
You're right.

15:30.329 --> 15:33.664
Apples are better
than strawberries.

15:33.733 --> 15:37.167
Only if by "better" you mean
"better at being disgusting."

15:37.236 --> 15:39.770
You'd better apologize!

15:39.839 --> 15:41.038
Oh, I'm sorry...

15:41.107 --> 15:43.107
that you actually bite
into those tasteless,

15:43.176 --> 15:44.609
mealy, worm-filled things.

15:46.779 --> 15:48.112
What?

15:48.181 --> 15:50.014
[growl]

15:50.083 --> 15:51.048
Applejack!

15:51.117 --> 15:52.416
Why are you so angry?

15:52.485 --> 15:55.152
It's just Strawberry's
honest opinion.

15:55.221 --> 15:57.488
What's wrong with that?

15:57.557 --> 15:59.423
Well, that's fine if
she doesn't like 'em,

15:59.492 --> 16:02.259
but if she knew how hard we
work to make our apples perfect,

16:02.328 --> 16:07.031
maybe she wouldn't be so
mean about it--Oooooh.

16:07.100 --> 16:08.265
Oh, boy.

16:08.334 --> 16:09.500
Mmm-hmm.

16:09.569 --> 16:10.801
Doesn't feel so good, does it?

16:10.870 --> 16:12.469
No.

16:12.538 --> 16:14.705
No, it does not at all.

16:14.774 --> 16:18.075
I am so sorry, Rarity.

16:18.144 --> 16:20.444
I got so carried away
with bein' honest,

16:20.513 --> 16:23.447
I guess I didn't think about
how I was makin' others feel.

16:23.516 --> 16:26.583
I'm a real rotten apple.

16:26.652 --> 16:28.252
I appreciate that, Applejack.

16:28.321 --> 16:29.586
That means a lot.

16:29.655 --> 16:31.055
I just wish you'd realized it

16:31.124 --> 16:33.123
before you ruined
the fashion show!

16:33.192 --> 16:39.129
♪♪

16:39.198 --> 16:41.231
I need to get some of these.

16:41.300 --> 16:42.633
It's the only way to travel.

16:45.371 --> 16:47.104
What are you doing?

16:47.173 --> 16:49.339
Canterlot is that way.

16:49.408 --> 16:52.010
Yep but you're not goin'
back to Canterlot yet.

16:54.780 --> 16:56.213
Hey!

16:56.282 --> 16:57.347
What is she...

16:57.416 --> 16:58.649
I don't know.

16:58.718 --> 16:59.751
Run!

17:10.296 --> 17:11.628
Listen, y'all.

17:11.697 --> 17:13.230
I thought I was
just bein' honest

17:13.299 --> 17:14.765
when I said all those things,

17:14.834 --> 17:18.769
but somepony helped me realize
I was actually bein' hurtful.

17:18.838 --> 17:22.306
So for that, I apologize.

17:22.375 --> 17:26.143
So you don't think
fashion is ridiculous?

17:26.212 --> 17:30.614
Well... I... still don't
understand it,

17:30.683 --> 17:33.450
but I appreciate how much
it means to y'all

17:33.519 --> 17:35.719
and how much hard
work you put into it.

17:35.788 --> 17:38.589
I also know this contest
is important to Rarity.

17:38.658 --> 17:40.191
So what do you say?

17:43.529 --> 17:45.796
I'd hate to have come
all this way here

17:45.865 --> 17:48.332
and not see what
you can do.

17:48.401 --> 17:50.267
If they're judging, we're in.

17:50.336 --> 17:51.768
Under one condition.

17:51.837 --> 17:53.270
Literally.

17:53.339 --> 17:54.471
Anything.

17:54.540 --> 17:56.174
Untie us.

18:04.784 --> 18:07.184
Show's back on, fellas!

18:07.253 --> 18:08.585
[groan]

18:08.654 --> 18:12.856
♪♪

18:12.925 --> 18:14.491
Ah!

18:14.560 --> 18:24.268
♪♪

18:24.337 --> 18:25.436
[crash]

18:27.006 --> 18:28.772
[laughter]

18:28.841 --> 18:31.708
♪♪

18:31.777 --> 18:32.709
Uh uh.

18:32.778 --> 18:39.750
♪♪

18:39.819 --> 18:41.418
Uh huh.

18:41.487 --> 18:48.192
♪♪

18:48.261 --> 18:50.494
... and then Applejack found me
and told me to distract you

18:50.563 --> 18:51.828
for an hour but the hour's up!

18:51.897 --> 18:52.897
Ta da!

18:53.933 --> 18:55.699
But... how?

18:55.768 --> 18:57.334
They were all leaving...

18:57.403 --> 18:59.436
This was all coming down.

18:59.505 --> 19:00.904
You can thank Applejack.

19:00.973 --> 19:02.272
She<u> lit'rally</u> did
it all by herself.

19:02.341 --> 19:05.609
I don't think that word means
what you think it means.

19:05.678 --> 19:10.781
But I did bust my tail because I
know how much this means to you.

19:10.850 --> 19:11.982
Ohh!

19:12.051 --> 19:13.817
Thank you, Applejack.

19:13.886 --> 19:14.919
We start now!

19:18.391 --> 19:20.424
First up, Lily Lace!

19:20.493 --> 19:27.998
♪♪

19:28.067 --> 19:29.366
Starstreak!

19:29.435 --> 19:37.574
♪♪

19:37.643 --> 19:38.976
Inky Rose!

19:39.045 --> 19:47.784
♪♪

19:47.853 --> 19:49.886
And now it's time to vote.

19:49.955 --> 19:52.789
I am drawn to the beauty
and drama of fashion

19:52.858 --> 19:55.759
and no pony does drama
better than Lily Lace.

19:55.828 --> 19:57.794
So I vote for her.

19:57.863 --> 20:02.300
It means soooo much to me,
I literally can't even...

20:03.436 --> 20:06.570
Simplicity is the
keynote of true elegance.

20:06.639 --> 20:10.941
That is why I vote
for Inky Rose.

20:11.010 --> 20:14.412
You've made me so happy.

20:16.482 --> 20:17.781
Fashion is the art!

20:17.850 --> 20:21.418
I, Photo Finish,
vote for Starstreak!

20:21.487 --> 20:23.720
Wonderful to hear, darling.

20:23.789 --> 20:26.556
Well, it all comes
down to you, Applejack.

20:26.625 --> 20:28.592
Can you believe it!

20:28.661 --> 20:29.860
After everything
that's happened,

20:29.929 --> 20:31.728
Applejack is the
deciding vote!

20:31.797 --> 20:33.930
Ah! This is so exciting!

20:33.999 --> 20:37.467
Well, Applejack?

20:37.536 --> 20:42.639
Uh, uh...

20:42.708 --> 20:46.543
Lily Lace's clothes go here,
Inky Rose's will go there

20:46.612 --> 20:48.378
and Starstreak's there.

20:48.447 --> 20:50.814
Sorry, but I couldn't
pick just one.

20:50.883 --> 20:52.949
They all did great
and in my opinion,

20:53.018 --> 20:54.651
they all deserve to win.

20:54.720 --> 20:55.986
And I agree.

20:56.055 --> 20:59.022
I told you your perspective
would be beneficial.

20:59.091 --> 21:02.392
Is this one of your
new designs, Rarity?

21:02.461 --> 21:03.727
It's, uh...

21:03.796 --> 21:06.630
the form is reminiscent of...

21:06.699 --> 21:09.966
I mean, it conjures
up images of...

21:10.035 --> 21:11.968
Well, uh..I mean...

21:12.037 --> 21:13.069
Oh, that?

21:13.138 --> 21:15.806
No, I totally
messed that one up.

21:15.875 --> 21:17.007
It's ghastly.

21:17.076 --> 21:18.041
Horrid.

21:18.110 --> 21:19.910
Absolutely terrible.

21:19.979 --> 21:22.512
Oh, thank goodness.

21:22.581 --> 21:26.416
Cause in my honest
opinion, it's awful.

21:26.485 --> 21:29.386
[hearty laughter]

21:29.455 --> 21:31.455
When you're right,
you're right.
